Description: Fragments from a relief plaque; eight; bone; the largest depicts a reclining nude female, part of a nereid riding a triton.
Bibliographic references: Petrie at al 1915 / Heliopolis, Kafr Ammar and Shurafa (p. 43, pl. L.4 (right half))
Acquisition name: Donated by: British School of Archaeology, Egypt
Acquisition notes: Register says found c.6 miles south of Helouan.
